  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 16\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dde\u0d9b\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0db8\u0dab\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Madrigiri received fuel after 16 days only for health",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "After 16 days, Madrigiriya cooperative fuel station was given only to the employees of the health department.",
        "This situation arose when the filling station workers did not give fuel to any person who had been waiting in the queue for many days.",
        "This gas station finally received fuel on the 30th of June and with the receipt of 6600 liters of fuel today, the health department, with the approval of the district secretary, distributed about 2000 liters of this fuel stock to Madirigiri Base Hospital staff and 500 liters of fuel for essential services and the remaining 4100 liters of fuel in Attanakada. The filling station manager Mr. Saman Kumara told Lankadeepa that it was mentioned in the letter that Alahera, Bakamoona etc. hospitals should be segregated.",
        "According to that, a fuel stock of 2500 rupees was issued for an employee who reports to work by motorcycle and tricycle and for a person who comes by car, fuel was issued in the amount of 7000 rupees.",
        "The people who were staying in Polim said that although it is mandatory to issue fuel to the health staff to come to the hospital for work, if there is no fuel to bring a patient to the hospital, he will even have to die at home.",
        "Due to that, they insisted to provide fuel to all the people.",
        "Polonnaruwa District Health Services Director W.K. Although he tried to negotiate with Mr. WS Kumaramwansa, all those opportunities failed."
      ],
